# Auth & Data Access Security

All auth is handled by Clerk. Every server-side operation that touches the database **must** verify the current user and scope queries to their data.

## Getting the Current User

```typescript
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized"); // or redirect to sign-in
```

## Scoping Queries to the Current User

Always filter by `clerkUserId` when reading or mutating decks. Never trust IDs from client input alone.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — fetches any deck by ID, no ownership check
const deck = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.id, deckId));

// ✅ GOOD — scoped to the authenticated user
const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

const deck = await db
  .select()
  .from(decks)
  .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));

if (!deck.length) throw new Error("Not found"); // treat as not found, not forbidden
```

## Cards Are Owned Transitively via Decks

Cards don't have a `clerkUserId` — join through `decks` to verify ownership:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — verify deck ownership before operating on its cards
const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

const [deck] = await db
  .select()
  .from(decks)
  .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));

if (!deck) throw new Error("Not found");

// safe to read/write cards for this deck
```

## Rules

- Always call `auth()` at the top of every server action or route handler
- Never skip the `clerkUserId` filter on `decks` queries
- Treat unauthorized access as "not found" (don't leak existence of other users' data)
- Never use a `deckId` or `cardId` from the client without verifying ownership first
